WEBVTT

00:00:02.980 --> 00:00:05.230
Satono Group G1 Association

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:11.100
There's not long now until the
first race of the Fall G1 season.

00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:14.240
Yes. I'm going to make
sure I win the Kikkashou.

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:17.990
We'll be rooting for you, so do your best.

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:22.340
Of course. I'll do everything I can to
deliver a G1 victory to the Satono family.

00:00:22.340 --> 00:00:25.350
That sounds promising! We'll
be looking forward to it.

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:26.250
If you'll excuse us.

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:30.170
It should be quite a race.

00:00:30.170 --> 00:00:33.110
The old men have their hopes
pinned on you, as usual.

00:00:33.110 --> 00:00:35.360
How are you feeling heading
into the Kikkashou?

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:39.010
Good so far. Crown-chan, are you
going on another overseas excursion?

00:00:39.010 --> 00:00:42.060
First, I'll be running in the Fall Tennoushou.

00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:43.290
Let's both do our best.

00:00:43.290 --> 00:00:44.190
Right!

00:00:44.190 --> 00:00:46.900
Crown lost the Satsukishou due to
her trouble running diagonally.

00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:50.860
Dia's Satsukishou went the same way,
and in the Derby, her shoe broke...

00:00:50.860 --> 00:00:52.920
It makes me wonder how the
Kikkashou will turn out.

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:56.910
Dia has all of the necessary ability,
but still couldn't win...

00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:58.910
I suppose it's just the Satono jinx.

00:00:58.910 --> 00:01:02.710
Maybe Satono horse girls
really can't win G1 races.

00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:03.790
Crown-chan...

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:04.930
But they...

00:01:04.930 --> 00:01:06.620
It's the results that matter.

00:01:10.800 --> 00:01:14.820
Episode 6
\hDiamond

00:01:18.270 --> 00:01:20.170
Dia seems fired up.

00:01:20.170 --> 00:01:21.690
She's in really good shape.

00:01:21.690 --> 00:01:23.330
At this rate, the 3,000-meter distance

00:01:23.330 --> 00:01:26.690
and hills of the Kikkashou
shouldn't be any problem.

00:01:26.690 --> 00:01:29.210
The final race of the classic Triple Crown.

00:01:29.210 --> 00:01:30.850
This time, she can win!

00:01:30.850 --> 00:01:32.440
I think so too.

00:01:34.940 --> 00:01:37.190
The Satsukishou, the Derby...

00:01:37.190 --> 00:01:39.950
I was in perfect condition, physically
and mentally, both times.

00:01:40.500 --> 00:01:43.500
I thought the jinx was
nothing to worry about...

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:47.210
I was going to win and prove that.

00:01:47.210 --> 00:01:48.040
And yet...

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:51.000
Whoa, and on the outside, it's Divinity!

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.570
Divinity is making a lot of sudden headway!

00:01:53.570 --> 00:01:59.200
Number eight, Satono Diamond, put up a
great fight but came a step short!

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:10.120
If running fast and being
strong isn't enough...

00:02:10.680 --> 00:02:13.090
I'll take the jinx on.

00:02:15.070 --> 00:02:16.240
Time to eat!

00:02:16.240 --> 00:02:19.450
It's time for today's last two horoscopes.

00:02:19.550 --> 00:02:21.050
Horoscopes

00:02:19.860 --> 00:02:23.210
In 11th place is Aquarius.

00:02:21.050 --> 00:02:22.200
11th Place
Aquarius

00:02:23.210 --> 00:02:26.320
No matter what you try,
it's going to go poorly today.

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:28.080
Aquarius

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:28.080
No matter what you try today, it won't go well

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:28.080
Your unlucky color:     red

00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:28.080
You should be careful around red things.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:29.850
Red...

00:02:31.210 --> 00:02:33.710
Shichimi
Seasoning

00:02:31.210 --> 00:02:33.710
Table
Pepper

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:45.980
With that much shichimi peppers in it, I don't think
you can even drink the soup anymore—

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:54.360
Are you okay, Dia-chan?!

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:58.150
Aquarius

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:58.150
No matter what you try today, it won't go well

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:58.150
Your unlucky color:     red

00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:55.970
Sure, I'm fine.

00:02:56.290 --> 00:02:58.730
Sorry, Kita-chan, but I'm gonna
head out early today.

00:02:58.730 --> 00:03:00.260
O-Okay.

00:03:00.070 --> 00:03:00.820
Aquarius

00:03:00.070 --> 00:03:00.820
No matter what you try today, it won't go well

00:03:00.070 --> 00:03:00.820
Your unlucky color:     red

00:03:03.550 --> 00:03:05.860
I wonder what's gotten into her?

00:03:05.860 --> 00:03:08.170
And in last place is Pisces.

00:03:08.170 --> 00:03:09.580
That's me!

00:03:09.580 --> 00:03:11.210
Stats Are Good, But So Are Fortunes

00:03:09.580 --> 00:03:11.210
Best Value

00:03:11.210 --> 00:03:14.210
Fukukitaru-san, could you
tell my fortune, please?

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:16.620
Yep, yep, mhmm.

00:03:16.620 --> 00:03:17.900
Very well.

00:03:18.330 --> 00:03:19.340
It's bad.

00:03:20.370 --> 00:03:23.020
You must avoid heading eastward.
It will bring bad fortune.

00:03:23.020 --> 00:03:26.140
Unlucky things will happen around you.

00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:27.370
East, then?

00:03:27.370 --> 00:03:29.550
Correct. Avoid the east at all costs.

00:03:29.550 --> 00:03:30.430
It's very bad luck!

00:03:30.430 --> 00:03:32.950
Fuku-chan-senpai, isn't there
anything she can do?

00:03:32.950 --> 00:03:34.950
Is there any hope?

00:03:34.950 --> 00:03:36.090
Not to worry!

00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.730
Hope lies in the west!

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:38.900
Never mind that.

00:03:39.320 --> 00:03:41.020
Thank you for your help.

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:45.570
Does she not need hope?!

00:03:48.050 --> 00:03:51.100
What was Dia-chan up to this morning?

00:03:52.530 --> 00:03:54.080
Dia-chan?

00:03:55.730 --> 00:03:58.000
This way is east.

00:04:00.860 --> 00:04:01.800
Dia-chan?!

00:04:05.080 --> 00:04:06.500
It'll take more than this...

00:04:09.810 --> 00:04:12.700
Good! That takes care of
Fukukitaru-san's fortune.

00:04:12.700 --> 00:04:13.550
Next!

00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:17.520
Fortune?

00:04:19.900 --> 00:04:22.740
C
o
p
a
n
o

00:04:19.900 --> 00:04:22.740
You want to know how to summon bad luck?

00:04:22.740 --> 00:04:25.390
Yes. What kind of things should I do?

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:29.670
Well, feng shui is pretty
helpful in avoiding bad luck!

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:30.980
So leave it to me.

00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:33.620
I'll explain it to you, rickety-split!

00:04:35.370 --> 00:04:39.750
Dia-chan, areas with a lot of wood
seem to be bad for you at the moment.

00:04:39.750 --> 00:04:41.380
They might mean bad luck.

00:04:41.730 --> 00:04:43.870
A lot of wood, then...

00:04:45.380 --> 00:04:46.970
Thank you.

00:04:46.970 --> 00:04:48.140
You be careful!

00:04:48.140 --> 00:04:49.680
Coppa-careful!

00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:51.140
Feng shui?

00:04:54.140 --> 00:04:57.590
A place with a lot of wood... This should do.

00:04:57.590 --> 00:05:00.200
Another day of training!

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:01.850
Let's dash, dash, dash!

00:05:01.850 --> 00:05:03.530
Dash, dash, dash!

00:05:03.530 --> 00:05:05.200
Dash! Dash!

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:06.870
Dash-ash-ash!

00:05:06.870 --> 00:05:08.550
Dash, dash, dash!

00:05:08.550 --> 00:05:10.340
Dash, dash, dash!

00:05:10.340 --> 00:05:11.040
Dash!

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:11.950
Dash!

00:05:11.950 --> 00:05:12.450
Da—

00:05:12.450 --> 00:05:13.040
shing!

00:05:13.040 --> 00:05:14.410
Shing?!

00:05:15.620 --> 00:05:17.000
Bakushin O-san?!

00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:20.010
Good. That takes care of
Rickey-san's feng shui.

00:05:20.010 --> 00:05:20.850
Next!

00:05:21.170 --> 00:05:23.170
Library

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:25.670
Let's see here...

00:05:25.670 --> 00:05:30.350
The Seven Wonders of
Tracen Academy
100 Entries

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:29.280
"If you play the piano in
the music room at 4:44,

00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:33.100
a ghost with only legs will appear"?

00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:33.100
Seven Wonders of Tracen Academy

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:35.600
Okay...

00:05:35.810 --> 00:05:38.400
Where'd Dia-chan get to now?

00:06:01.380 --> 00:06:06.470
Please don't play the piano

00:06:02.580 --> 00:06:06.470
Well, I didn't run into any
leg ghost... Another one down.

00:06:09.020 --> 00:06:11.220
A leg ghost!

00:06:13.470 --> 00:06:16.340
Dia-chan... what's going on with her today?

00:06:17.370 --> 00:06:18.600
I'm home.

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:20.090
Welcome back, Kita-chan.

00:06:25.320 --> 00:06:27.960
What's with the critters, Dia-chan?!

00:06:27.960 --> 00:06:30.580
They've been helping me train a bit.

00:06:30.580 --> 00:06:31.660
Th-They have?

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:35.200
Right. Crows and black cats
are considered ominous, right?

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:36.830
So when it comes to jinxes—

00:06:38.730 --> 00:06:41.720
My collection!

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:44.290
So you're training to beat the jinx?

00:06:44.510 --> 00:06:45.290
Right.

00:06:45.290 --> 00:06:46.470
I started thinking...

00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:50.410
If the Satono jinx is real, then being
strong won't be enough to break it.

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:53.910
Which is why I'm training to
defeat all kinds of jinxes,

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:56.650
so that I can be ready no matter
what happens at the Kikkashou!

00:06:56.650 --> 00:07:01.100
That explains the black
cat and crow, I guess.

00:07:01.430 --> 00:07:03.800
But don't overdo it, okay?

00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:07.190
It's all right. You worry too much, Kita-chan.

00:07:07.440 --> 00:07:09.170
I should go and run.

00:07:09.170 --> 00:07:10.850
But it's so late!

00:07:10.850 --> 00:07:14.230
True. But I didn't train enough this morning.

00:07:14.230 --> 00:07:15.560
See you later.

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.200
Take care.

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:31.550
Seven Wonders of Tracen Academy

00:07:27.300 --> 00:07:31.550
If you drink a 666ml glass of honey drink, misfortune will befall you

00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:55.990
Seven Wonders of Tracen Academy

00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:55.990
Those who are on the campus grounds at the stroke
of midnight will be unable to return home

00:08:20.680 --> 00:08:23.190
What is the Kikkashou?

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:30.440
Kikkashou

00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:40.900
I'll overcome whatever comes my way!

00:08:41.910 --> 00:08:44.870
And win a G1 for the Satono family!

00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:49.960
Umamusume

00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:49.960
Pretty Derby

00:09:00.130 --> 00:09:01.360
The Satono family...

00:09:03.610 --> 00:09:08.420
Our family has contributed a great deal
to the sport of horse girl racing,

00:09:08.420 --> 00:09:13.320
from working with the administration
to participating in charitable works.

00:09:14.250 --> 00:09:18.070
But the greatest achievement
in the field of racing,

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:22.730
fielding a horse girl that can
win a G1 race, has proved elusive.

00:09:23.450 --> 00:09:24.960
Field Day

00:09:23.770 --> 00:09:26.960
I was lucky enough to be born
with a talent for running.

00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:30.960
People would watch me race.

00:09:31.660 --> 00:09:34.970
When I made first place,
they would be happy.

00:09:35.400 --> 00:09:38.970
When I was young, that made
me happier than anything else.

00:09:40.190 --> 00:09:43.850
It was natural for me to yearn
for this particular dream.

00:09:44.350 --> 00:09:50.210
To pursue a G1 victory, the way
the older Satono girls were doing.

00:09:51.160 --> 00:09:52.000
But...

00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:04.870
Waiting Room

00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:17.170
I really did try my hardest.

00:10:20.090 --> 00:10:22.680
But I didn't come close... to winning a G1.

00:10:30.970 --> 00:10:32.610
I'm sorry, Dia.

00:10:33.510 --> 00:10:36.140
Everyone's going to pin
their hopes on you now.

00:10:40.170 --> 00:10:43.300
I shouldered the unfulfilled
dreams and frustrations

00:10:43.300 --> 00:10:45.120
of my family as they left the turf.

00:10:45.120 --> 00:10:47.460
I started to feel more strongly...

00:10:48.430 --> 00:10:50.540
That I would win, for all their sakes.

00:10:51.070 --> 00:10:55.510
That I would bring victory...
and hope to the Satono family.

00:10:56.760 --> 00:10:57.960
And yet...

00:10:58.810 --> 00:11:01.400
Even Dia-san couldn't win.

00:11:01.400 --> 00:11:05.390
She's so strong, but keeps having
bad luck at the last second.

00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:08.270
The Satono jinx has to be real.

00:11:08.270 --> 00:11:11.400
No matter how hard we try,
we can't win G1 races.

00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:14.730
Is there any point to us even debuting?

00:11:16.320 --> 00:11:18.170
I have to win.

00:11:18.170 --> 00:11:21.240
Win and bring hope to them!

00:11:23.900 --> 00:11:24.820
It's on me.

00:11:31.160 --> 00:11:33.580
Training to break a jinx, huh?

00:11:33.580 --> 00:11:36.340
She's been training so
much longer than usual,

00:11:36.340 --> 00:11:39.450
and no matter what I ask,
she just says it's fine.

00:11:39.900 --> 00:11:42.190
I can't help but worry.

00:11:42.970 --> 00:11:45.000
You sure you've got time to
worry about someone else?

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:46.850
She's plenty strong! Don't sweat it!

00:11:46.850 --> 00:11:47.600
Still...

00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:49.670
Who doesn't worry about their friends?

00:11:49.670 --> 00:11:52.180
And unlike you, Kitasan actually cares!

00:11:52.180 --> 00:11:55.110
Say what?! Nobody cares more
about their friends than me!

00:11:55.110 --> 00:11:57.780
They call me "Golshi, the
friendliest horse girl"!

00:11:55.110 --> 00:11:58.280
Maybe you could give her
something to ward off bad luck?

00:11:57.780 --> 00:11:58.650
A sports drink would work!

00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:00.750
I see... chase off the bad luck, huh?

00:11:58.650 --> 00:11:59.430
It would.

00:12:00.750 --> 00:12:02.580
Then a good luck charm should do.

00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:04.110
And then maybe...

00:12:02.810 --> 00:12:04.110
A sports drink!

00:12:17.130 --> 00:12:18.590
One more time.

00:12:18.590 --> 00:12:20.370
You're certainly working hard.

00:12:21.380 --> 00:12:23.120
M-McQueen-san?!

00:12:23.120 --> 00:12:24.410
What are you doing here?

00:12:26.010 --> 00:12:28.510
Would you care for a chat?

00:12:33.790 --> 00:12:35.420
How are you feeling?

00:12:35.420 --> 00:12:36.810
Fantastic.

00:12:36.810 --> 00:12:39.040
The last race of the classic Triple Crown...

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:41.430
No matter what, I intend to win.

00:12:42.080 --> 00:12:44.380
Kitasan's worried about you.

00:12:44.780 --> 00:12:47.440
That's what got me wondering.

00:12:48.280 --> 00:12:51.940
H-Honestly, Kita-chan's such a worrywart.

00:12:51.940 --> 00:12:52.930
Gosh.

00:12:52.930 --> 00:12:53.940
Is she?

00:12:56.040 --> 00:12:58.460
You're sure you're not overdoing it?

00:13:03.690 --> 00:13:07.070
"Satono horse girls can't win G1 races."

00:13:07.070 --> 00:13:08.970
Have you heard that before?

00:13:09.460 --> 00:13:10.130
Yes.

00:13:11.450 --> 00:13:13.520
I didn't think it could be real.

00:13:13.950 --> 00:13:15.840
That it was foolish to even consider.

00:13:16.490 --> 00:13:18.880
I believed that for so long.

00:13:19.720 --> 00:13:20.730
But then...

00:13:21.700 --> 00:13:24.020
I can't keep losing.

00:13:24.740 --> 00:13:26.550
At the Kikkashou, finally...

00:13:26.550 --> 00:13:29.200
I'll break the Satono jinx, and then—

00:13:29.200 --> 00:13:32.360
Jinxes are the kind of thing someone
comes up with after the fact.

00:13:32.360 --> 00:13:33.950
That's what I believe.

00:13:38.120 --> 00:13:42.300
But that can't be! At the
Satsukishou, and the Derby, I—

00:13:42.300 --> 00:13:44.920
Then are you familiar with this one?

00:13:45.360 --> 00:13:48.720
"The strongest horse girls are
the ones who win the Kikkashou."

00:13:49.660 --> 00:13:51.220
I've heard it...

00:13:51.780 --> 00:13:54.400
If that jinx was true, that would mean that

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:59.860
Kitasan and I won the
Kikkashou because of it.

00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.830
That some strange power led us to victory.

00:14:02.830 --> 00:14:06.900
That's not true! You and Kita-chan
won because you're both strong!

00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:08.840
Not because of some jinx!

00:14:10.170 --> 00:14:12.900
And I believe that's all there is to it.

00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:15.360
Just a bit of nonsense
that someone thinks up.

00:14:15.790 --> 00:14:18.850
It's true that you ran into
misfortune this spring, Satono-san.

00:14:18.850 --> 00:14:23.210
But bad luck and shoe trouble
are common enough in racing.

00:14:23.900 --> 00:14:25.910
They... are?

00:14:25.910 --> 00:14:27.030
Of course.

00:14:27.030 --> 00:14:30.720
Considering that this is coming
from the Kikkashou winner

00:14:31.480 --> 00:14:36.820
who was considered so
dominant that it was boring...

00:14:36.820 --> 00:14:38.560
Surely you must be convinced.

00:14:40.010 --> 00:14:40.960
But the jinx—

00:14:40.960 --> 00:14:42.580
I know what it's like.

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:45.780
To race for your family's sake...

00:14:46.170 --> 00:14:48.950
The weight of running while
carrying your family's lineage.

00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:59.720
It's quite a burden, but you've
never run from that pain.

00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:03.480
You've looked forward through
the pain and given your all.

00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:06.190
That's not the kind of thing anyone can do.

00:15:07.550 --> 00:15:09.610
Your line was cut off on the track,

00:15:09.610 --> 00:15:12.030
which pushed you into third
place at the Satsukishou.

00:15:12.570 --> 00:15:17.100
And you were within a breadth of winning the
Japanese Derby, despite your shoe breaking.

00:15:17.770 --> 00:15:21.610
I honestly felt that you seemed
stronger than anyone else.

00:15:22.530 --> 00:15:26.420
The effort you've expended,
the feelings you've pursued...

00:15:26.420 --> 00:15:29.360
are not the kind of things that can be
blunted by a jinx someone concocted.

00:15:30.280 --> 00:15:31.850
McQueen-san...

00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:34.620
Please, believe in yourself.

00:15:34.910 --> 00:15:37.230
You are a strong horse girl.

00:15:37.610 --> 00:15:41.910
You'll need to rest properly so that you
can be at full strength for the race.

00:15:42.690 --> 00:15:44.630
And nothing else.

00:15:50.560 --> 00:15:52.630
Don't you see?

00:15:52.630 --> 00:15:55.440
Then perhaps I'll give you the
best piece of advice I know.

00:15:55.440 --> 00:15:58.570
A rabbit was looking at a turtle.
And the turtle—

00:15:57.270 --> 00:15:58.870
Can I ask you for one thing?

00:15:58.870 --> 00:16:00.020
What might that be?

00:16:02.880 --> 00:16:05.650
Please come to see the Kikkashou.

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:08.870
I'll cross the finish
line before anyone else.

00:16:09.700 --> 00:16:12.350
Right. I'll be looking forward to it.

00:16:14.020 --> 00:16:15.490
Thank you so much.

00:16:19.420 --> 00:16:22.210
I'm back... huh?

00:16:22.550 --> 00:16:24.000
Welcome back, Dia-chan.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:25.130
Kita-chan?

00:16:25.130 --> 00:16:27.220
What is all this?

00:16:27.220 --> 00:16:32.020
I gathered up a bunch of lucky
items to help you break the jinx.

00:16:32.330 --> 00:16:33.510
Here you go!

00:16:33.510 --> 00:16:36.010
Good luck

00:16:39.730 --> 00:16:42.480
Thanks. Sorry for worrying you.

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:45.020
But I'm okay now.

00:16:45.930 --> 00:16:47.300
That's a relief.

00:16:48.770 --> 00:16:52.850
In that case, let's toast to Dia's comeback!

00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:01.910
We've got a huge crowd here this
autumn at the Tokyo Racecourse,

00:17:01.910 --> 00:17:04.290
for the final act of the
classic Triple Crown...

00:17:04.570 --> 00:17:07.790
Which horse girl will
the spotlight shine down on?

00:17:08.060 --> 00:17:09.540
Three thousand meters of turf are waiting.

00:17:09.990 --> 00:17:12.550
All 18 runners are headed toward the gate.

00:17:14.890 --> 00:17:17.550
As they begin to enter...

00:17:18.020 --> 00:17:19.390
I believe.

00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.960
In the dreams that have been entrusted
to me, and my own strength,

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:24.930
that I've built from running so much—

00:17:31.320 --> 00:17:34.720
And the number 18 horse girl,
Royal Tartan, is now inside the gate.

00:17:35.450 --> 00:17:37.620
I am the strongest!

00:17:37.620 --> 00:17:40.840
And the Kikkashou has begun!

00:17:42.090 --> 00:17:44.700
It looks like number 17, Tip-of-Turn,
is off to a late start.

00:17:44.910 --> 00:17:48.570
Number two, Jakarta Funk, and number five,
Chief Parser, are moving up.

00:17:48.570 --> 00:17:49.960
They're passing the others.

00:17:50.840 --> 00:17:54.850
The featured number three, Satono Diamond,
is about five to six lengths from the lead.

00:17:55.510 --> 00:17:58.600
It's said that the the final race of the
classic Triple Crown, the Kikkashou,

00:17:58.600 --> 00:18:00.630
is won by the strongest horse girls.

00:18:00.630 --> 00:18:01.840
Do you know why?

00:18:01.840 --> 00:18:02.910
Because this race is—

00:18:02.910 --> 00:18:04.400
You told me this before.

00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:11.520
And now the horse girls are
entering the home stretch.

00:18:11.520 --> 00:18:13.320
Go!

00:18:13.710 --> 00:18:16.780
They clear the first 1,000
meters in 59.9 seconds!

00:18:16.780 --> 00:18:20.010
They pass the stands, bathed in applause,
as they enter the first corner.

00:18:20.010 --> 00:18:22.660
There are about 20 lengths from first
to last place, showing how tight the

00:18:22.930 --> 00:18:24.410
competition is going into the first corner.

00:18:22.930 --> 00:18:24.410
Go!

00:18:24.700 --> 00:18:28.670
Dia, give the Satono horse girls some hope!

00:18:29.110 --> 00:18:32.120
I know you can do this, Diamond-san.

00:18:32.950 --> 00:18:36.110
Eight hundred meters to go.
They're entering the third corner.

00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:38.640
Number five, Chief Parser, is out
in front with a clear lead.

00:18:41.180 --> 00:18:42.680
I'm carrying them.

00:18:42.680 --> 00:18:48.030
The frustrations, wishes, and hopes
of the Satono horse girls.

00:18:48.030 --> 00:18:52.600
I'll show it to them. With a
dazzling victory, the light of hope!

00:18:53.880 --> 00:18:58.460
I'll make it happen. My dream—
and the wish of my family!

00:19:00.150 --> 00:19:04.120
I am strong... stronger than anyone!

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:06.620
Dia-chan!

00:19:06.620 --> 00:19:09.690
And now number three,
Satono Diamond, is making her move!

00:19:09.690 --> 00:19:11.740
Number six, Divinity, also takes off.

00:19:11.740 --> 00:19:13.050
They're moving up next to each other.

00:19:13.050 --> 00:19:16.260
Chief Parser is trying to stay
in front with a two-length lead!

00:19:19.170 --> 00:19:20.430
Go!

00:19:20.710 --> 00:19:21.990
And now, the final straight!

00:19:21.990 --> 00:19:23.200
They've all begun their last spurt!

00:19:23.200 --> 00:19:25.690
The stands are quaking with cheers!

00:19:29.180 --> 00:19:30.960
Go!

00:19:30.960 --> 00:19:32.650
Go!

00:19:32.650 --> 00:19:34.400
Go!

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:36.150
Go!

00:19:49.160 --> 00:19:51.010
Number three, Satono Diamond,
is moving up on the outside.

00:19:51.010 --> 00:19:53.580
And number six, Divinity,
has a two-length lead!

00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:56.420
Original Shine was in the
rear and is also moving up!

00:19:55.450 --> 00:19:56.420
Dia-chan!

00:19:56.420 --> 00:20:00.300
She's out in front now! Number three,
Satono Diamond, is now in the lead!

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:02.550
On the inside is number 13, Jewel Spinel!

00:20:02.550 --> 00:20:04.510
On the outside, number 11, Original Shine!

00:20:04.510 --> 00:20:06.700
And number six, Divinity, is part of
the battle for second place!

00:20:06.700 --> 00:20:08.010
Satono Diamond!

00:20:08.010 --> 00:20:10.740
She has 100 meters left before making
her family's dream come true!

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:25.960
And Satono Diamond crosses the
goal in a definitive first place!

00:20:29.660 --> 00:20:33.210
She took off and accelerated
all the way down that straight!

00:20:33.210 --> 00:20:36.560
Just how strong is Satono Diamond?!

00:20:36.560 --> 00:20:39.820
The number three runner is
the uncontested winner!

00:20:39.820 --> 00:20:43.210
In the battle for second place,
we've got number 11, Original Shine,

00:20:41.920 --> 00:20:44.490
Dia-chan!

00:20:43.210 --> 00:20:45.400
on the outside, number 13,
Jewel Spinel, on the inside,

00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:46.970
and number six,
Divinity, between them.

00:20:46.970 --> 00:20:48.920
They were spread out across from each other.

00:20:56.350 --> 00:20:59.360
Tokyo

00:20:56.350 --> 00:20:59.360
Final

00:20:56.350 --> 00:20:59.360
Nose

00:21:12.620 --> 00:21:15.370
She did it! She did it!

00:21:16.305 --> 00:22:16.808
